article.headline: Colgate 70, Dartmouth 60
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Mark Linebaugh scored 17 points and dished out four assists to lead Colgate to a 70-60 win over visiting Dartmouth Monday. Alvin Reed scored 15 points and grabbed five rebounds for Colgate (9-7). Keith Williams added eight points and five rebounds. Colgate scored seven straight points to take a 12-6 lead with 12:34 left in the first half. They led the rest of the game. Leading 29-14 at the half, the Raiders increased their lead to as many as 21 points in the second half. Dartmouth (3-11) closed the game with a 15-4 run to cut the final deficit to 10 points. David Gardner led Dartmouth with 19 points and Leon Pattman added 10. The Raiders outrebounded the Big Green 39-22 and held them to 40.7 percent shooting. Colgate shot 51 percent from the field and hit 10 of 24 3-pointers.
